  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b86\u0b95\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bcd 9 \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bb2\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0baa\u0bca\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc7\u0b95\u0bbe",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "August 9 Strength of People's Struggle Will Teach President - Fonseka",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "On August 9th, everyone should come together in Colombo and teach the President the strength of the people's struggle.",
        "Field Marshal Sarath Fonseka told the meeting that Prime Minister Dinesh Gunawardena is likely to become the acting President.",
        "He mentioned the above while addressing the debate on the Emergency Act in Parliament on Wednesday (27).",
        "The emergency law was not implemented for the safety and livelihood of the people of the country, rather the emergency law was implemented to protect the corrupt politicians who are hated by the people. Freedom of expression is guaranteed by the constitution.",
        "Sri Lanka has become an unlivable country due to corrupt rulers. The cost of living is rising beyond the reach of the people. Fuel and gas shortages persist.",
        "It is completely wrong to label the people who are struggling on the streets as violent and rioters who are suffering from the cost of living and unlivable conditions.",
        "President Ranil Wickremesinghe when he was the Prime Minister mentioned that the state of crisis will last for three weeks and now he mentions that the state of crisis will last for one year. The people's struggle should not be ignored.",
        "The people's protest has boycotted the president who got the votes of 69 million people, the people's protest will soon boycott the president Ranil Wickremesinghe who was ignored by the people.",
        "People's struggle is justified. The Sri Lankan army has a unique reputation. Don't spoil the reputation by going against the people to protect the corrupt rulers, because 22 lakh people will be involved in the struggle.",
        "On the 9th of the coming month, all the people of the country should unite and strengthen the protest in Colombo. President Ranil Wickremesinghe should understand that the people's protest cannot be suppressed with power."
      ],
